<Layout title="Compliance — FERPA" description="701am compliance with FERPA and higher-education data protection standards.">
<header class="about-hero">
  <div class="hero-atmos"><div class="grid"></div><div class="glow g1"></div><div class="glow g2"></div><div class="glow g3"></div></div>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="eyebrow">Compliance</div>
    <h1>FERPA &amp; Higher-Ed <em class="grad">Standards</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">701am is designed for institutions that handle protected student information. We take FERPA compliance seriously — both as a legal obligation and as a trust requirement.</p>
  </div>
</header>

<article class="about-prose">
<div class="seg">Our FERPA posture</div>
<p>701am processes student-level data only as a <strong>school official</strong> with a legitimate educational interest, as defined by FERPA (34 CFR § 99.31). Our platform is configured to read program and enrollment metadata — never grades, disciplinary records, or personally identifiable student contact information unless explicitly authorized by the institution in writing.</p>
<p>We do not sell student data. We do not use student data for any purpose beyond operating the earned-media services for which it was disclosed. We do not share student data with unauthorized third parties.</p>

<div class="seg">Data minimized by design</div>
<p>701am works with the minimum data necessary to deliver earned-media visibility services. When connected to your CRM or SIS, we read:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Program names and identifiers</li>
  <li>Aggregate inquiry and application volumes</li>
  <li>Program-level outcomes data (e.g., placement rates, starting salaries)</li>
</ul>
<p>We do not access individual student names, email addresses, social security numbers, grades, or disciplinary records. Our integrations are read-only by default and revocable at any time.</p>

<div class="seg">Institutional control</div>
<p>Your institution retains full ownership and control of all data accessed through 701am. You may revoke integrations, delete workspaces, or request removal of your data at any time. Upon contract termination, all institutional data is permanently deleted within 90 days.</p>

<div class="seg">Data processing agreement</div>
<p>We enter into a FERPA-compliant data processing agreement with each institutional customer. This agreement reflects the requirements of the 2024 FERPA regulations and defines: the scope of data accessed, the purposes of processing, the prohibition on further disclosure, and the data safeguarding measures in place.</p>
<p>To request a copy of our DPA, contact <strong>legal@701am.com</strong>.</p>

<div class="seg">Data residency</div>
<p>All institutional data is processed and stored in the United States, in AWS US-East and US-West regions. No student-level data is transferred outside the United States.</p>

<div class="seg">Annual review</div>
<p>We review our FERPA compliance posture annually and upon any material change to our data practices. Our security infrastructure is audited as part of our SOC 2 readiness program.</p>

<div class="seg">Questions?</div>
<p>FERPA compliance questions can be directed to <strong>legal@701am.com</strong>. Our compliance team can provide a FERPA checklist, our DPA template, or walk through data flows with your privacy office.</p>
</article>

